---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

import '../../styles/global.css';

// Importing SEO data
import seoData from '@/data/js/services/containmentValidation';
---

<Layout
  seo={{
    title: `${seoData.meta.title} - Indivirtus`,
    description: seoData.meta.description,
    keywords: seoData.meta.keywords,
    canonical: seoData.meta.canonicalUrl,
    image: seoData.image.path.src,
    url: seoData.pageLink,
    schema: seoData.schema,
  }}
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 py-12 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <section class="mb-16 text-center">
      <h1 class="mb-6 text-4xl font-extrabold text-gray-900">Pharmaceutical Isolator Performance Verification</h1>
      <p class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-xl text-gray-600">
        Ensuring operator and environmental safety when handling potent compounds through rigorous containment
        validation protocols.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-8">
        <a href="/contact-us" class="button"> Request Consultation </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Main Content -->
    <article class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
      <!-- Introduction -->
      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800">Comprehensive Containment Validation for Potent Compounds</h2>
        <p>
          In pharmaceutical manufacturing facilities handling potent compounds (OEB 3+), proper isolator performance is
          critical for protecting both operators and the environment. Our containment validation services verify that
          your pharmaceutical isolators effectively contain these hazardous materials according to the highest industry
          standards.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Why It Matters -->
      <section class="mb-12 rounded-lg bg-blue-50 p-6">
        <h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800">The Importance of Isolator Performance Verification</h2>
        <p>
          Pharmaceutical isolators serve as the primary barrier between potent compounds and personnel/environment.
          Without proper verification:
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-4 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
          <li>Operators may be exposed to hazardous compounds</li>
          <li>Cross-contamination risks increase significantly</li>
          <li>Regulatory compliance may be compromised</li>
          <li>Environmental contamination could occur</li>
          <li>Product quality may be affected</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4">
          Our verification process ensures your containment systems perform as intended, mitigating these risks through
          scientific testing and analysis.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Our Methodology -->
      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800">Our ISPE SMEPAC-Compliant Verification Process</h2>
        <p>
          We follow a rigorous methodology aligned with ISPE SMEPAC guidelines and cGMP requirements to deliver
          reliable, defensible results:
        </p>

        <div class="mt-8 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-3">
          <div class="rounded-lg border border-gray-100 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm">
            <h3 class="mb-3 text-xl font-semibold text-blue-600">1. Performance Target Definition</h3>
            <p>
              We establish appropriate containment performance targets based on your specific compounds, processes, and
              risk assessments.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-lg border border-gray-100 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm">
            <h3 class="mb-3 text-xl font-semibold text-blue-600">2. Surrogate Powder Testing</h3>
            <p>
              Using scientifically validated surrogate materials, we simulate worst-case scenarios to challenge your
              isolator's containment capabilities.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-lg border border-gray-100 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm">
            <h3 class="mb-3 text-xl font-semibold text-blue-600">3. Comprehensive Sampling</h3>
            <p>
              Our Certified Industrial Hygienists collect air, personal, and surface samples at all critical points to
              identify potential leakage.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-6 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
          <div class="rounded-lg border border-gray-100 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm">
            <h3 class="mb-3 text-xl font-semibold text-blue-600">4. AIHA-Accredited Analysis</h3>
            <p>
              Samples are analyzed by AIHA-accredited laboratories using validated methods to ensure accurate, reliable
              results.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-lg border border-gray-100 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm">
            <h3 class="mb-3 text-xl font-semibold text-blue-600">5. Detailed Reporting</h3>
            <p>
              You receive comprehensive documentation including test protocols, raw data, analysis, and recommendations
              for compliance.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Industry Standards -->
      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800">Compliance with Industry Standards</h2>
        <p>Our verification services align with all major regulatory and industry guidelines:</p>
        <div class="mt-6 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-3">
          <div class="flex items-center rounded bg-gray-50 px-4 py-3">
            <svg class="mr-2 h-5 w-5 text-green-500" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"></path>
            </svg>
            <span>ISPE SMEPAC Guidelines</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center rounded bg-gray-50 px-4 py-3">
            <svg class="mr-2 h-5 w-5 text-green-500" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"></path>
            </svg>
            <span>cGMP Requirements</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center rounded bg-gray-50 px-4 py-3">
            <svg class="mr-2 h-5 w-5 text-green-500" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"></path>
            </svg>
            <span>OSHA Standards</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center rounded bg-gray-50 px-4 py-3">
            <svg class="mr-2 h-5 w-5 text-green-500" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"></path>
            </svg>
            <span>AIHA Protocols</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center rounded bg-gray-50 px-4 py-3">
            <svg class="mr-2 h-5 w-5 text-green-500" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"></path>
            </svg>
            <span>ISO 14644 Standards</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center rounded bg-gray-50 px-4 py-3">
            <svg class="mr-2 h-5 w-5 text-green-500" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"></path>
            </svg>
            <span>EU GMP Annex 1</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- FAQ Section -->
      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="mb-6 text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div title="">
            <p></p>
          </div>
          <div title="">
            <p></p>
          </div>
          <div title="">
            <p></p>
          </div>
          <div title="">
            <p></p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="mb-8 text-center text-3xl font-bold text-blue-800">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

        <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-lg bg-white shadow-md">
          <div class="border-b border-gray-200 p-6">
            <h3 class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold text-blue-700">How often should isolator performance be verified?</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              We recommend annual verification as a minimum, with more frequent testing following significant changes to
              equipment, processes, or when handling new compounds. Some high-risk applications may require quarterly
              verification.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="border-b border-gray-200 p-6">
            <h3 class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold text-blue-700">What surrogate materials do you use for testing?</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              We select surrogate materials based on your specific compounds and processes. Common choices include
              lactose monohydrate, mannitol, or other powders with similar particle size distribution to your active
              ingredients. All surrogates are thoroughly characterized for testing validity.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="border-b border-gray-200 p-6">
            <h3 class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold text-blue-700">
              Can you help us establish appropriate performance targets?
            </h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              Absolutely. Our team of Certified Industrial Hygienists will work with you to establish scientifically
              defensible performance targets based on your compounds' occupational exposure bands (OEB), toxicity data,
              and regulatory requirements.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="border-b border-gray-200 p-6">
            <h3 class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold text-blue-700">What happens if our isolator fails verification?</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              In case of performance issues, we provide detailed recommendations for corrective actions ranging from
              operational adjustments to equipment modifications. We can also assist with retesting after improvements
              are implemented.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- CTA Section -->
      <section class="rounded-xl bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-indigo-50 py-12 text-center">
        <h2 class="mb-4 text-3xl font-bold text-gray-800">Ready to Verify Your Isolator Performance?</h2>
        <p class="mx-auto mb-8 max-w-2xl text-xl text-gray-600">
          Ensure your containment systems are properly protecting your workforce and environment.
        </p>
        <a href="/contact-us" class="button"> Request Consultation </a>
      </section>
    </article>
  </div>

  <style is:global>
    /* Custom styles for better readability */
    .prose h2,
    .prose h3 {
      scroll-margin-top: 100px;
    }
    .prose ul {
      padding-left: 1.5rem;
      list-style-type: disc;
    }
  </style>
</Layout>
